                    <div class="mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-50 to-pink-100 p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                        <h3 class="font-bold flex items-center text-pink-700">
                            <i data-lucide="coins" class="mr-2" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"></i>
                            Cryptocurrency & Blockchain: The Dynamic Duo
                        </h3>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-white p-3 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Technical Definitions:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Cryptocurrency:</span> A digital form of money that uses cryptography for security and operates independently of central banks.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Blockchain:</span> A decentralized, distributed ledger that records all transactions across a network of computers.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Decentralization:</span> The distribution of control away from a central authority to a network of users.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-pink-50 p-3 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Cryptocurrency:</span> Like Taylor Swift going independent - no record label (central bank) needed! Your crypto is your music, and you're in complete control of your hits! 🎵</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Blockchain:</span> Like Taylor's loyal Swifties documenting every move she makes, with everyone having a copy of her entire career history - no one can change or deny what happened! 📝</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Decentralization:</span> Like when Taylor's fans collectively decide on tour setlists instead of just the management - power to the people! 🙌</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-white p-3 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Try it yourself:</p>
                            <div class="space-y-2">
                                <p class="text-gray-700"><span class="font-semibold">Real Example:</span> Open your phone's calculator and type 1 BTC = $65,000. Now imagine that value is controlled not by a bank, but by millions of people agreeing on its worth - just like how Taylor's songs become hits because fans collectively stream them millions of times!</p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700"><span class="font-semibold">Quick Exercise:</span> Visit CoinGecko.com and look up Bitcoin's price history for the last year. Notice how the value changes based on collective user activity - just like how streaming numbers affect an artist's chart position! 📈</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-50 to-pink-100 p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                        <h3 class="font-bold flex items-center text-pink-700">
                            <i data-lucide="wallet" class="mr-2" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"></i>
                            Wallets & Keys: Your Digital Backstage Pass
                        </h3>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-white p-3 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Technical Definitions:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Wallet:</span> A digital tool used to store, send, and receive cryptocurrencies, with Uniswap being a popular platform for managing and trading tokens.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Public Key:</span> Your shareable address for receiving cryptocurrency on Uniswap and other platforms.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Private Key:</span> Your secret key that gives access to your cryptocurrency and Uniswap trading activities.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-pink-50 p-3 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">Your Uniswap wallet is like your all-access festival pass - it lets you trade, swap, and store your digital assets. The public key is like your festival wristband ID that everyone can see and send tokens to. The private key? That's your secret VIP code that lets you access the exclusive trading areas - never share it, or someone else could take control of your crypto collection!</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-white p-3 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Try it yourself:</p>
                            <div class="space-y-2">
                                <p class="text-gray-700"><span class="font-semibold">Real Example:</span> Visit app.uniswap.org and connect your first wallet. Your wallet address will look something like "0x123...abc" - this is your public profile for receiving any ERC-20 tokens, just like having a universal username for all crypto festivals!</p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700"><span class="font-semibold">Quick Exercise:</span> After connecting to Uniswap, try swapping a small amount of ETH for another token. It's like exchanging your festival tokens for different types of VIP passes - but remember to keep your recovery phrase safe and never share it! 🔐</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-50 to-pink-100 p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                        <h3 class="font-bold flex items-center text-pink-700">
                            <i data-lucide="cpu" class="mr-2" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"></i>
                            Mining & Consensus: The Beat of the Blockchain
                        </h3>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-white p-3 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Technical Definitions:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Mining:</span> The process of creating new cryptocurrency and validating transactions.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Why Mining?</span> Mining ensures network security and transaction verification while controlling the release of new coins.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Proof-of-Work (PoW):</span> Miners solve complex puzzles to validate transactions.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Why PoW?</span> It prevents fraud by making it extremely expensive and computationally difficult to manipulate the network.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Proof-of-Stake (PoS):</span> Validators are chosen based on the amount of cryptocurrency they stake.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Why PoS?</span> It provides network security while being more energy-efficient and scalable than PoW.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Gas Fees:</span> Transaction fees paid to process transactions on the network.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-pink-50 p-3 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Mining & Why:</span> Like producing a hit song - it takes serious studio time and equipment (computing power) to create new tracks (coins)! We need this process to make sure every new song (transaction) is legit and maintain the value of the hits! 🎵</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">PoW & Why:</span> Think of it like American Idol's intense audition process - contestants (miners) must prove their dedication through hard work. This makes it super expensive to cheat, just like how it's impossible to fake your way through a live performance! 🎤</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">PoS & Why:</span> Like The Voice's coaching system - the more successful and invested you are (the more coins you stake), the more influence you have! It's like choosing experienced artists as judges instead of making them sing every time - way more efficient! 🌟</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Gas Fees:</span> Like Ticketmaster service charges - these fees keep the show running and reward the people maintaining the venue (network)! 💸</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-white p-3 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Try it yourself:</p>
                            <div class="space-y-2">
                                <p class="text-gray-700"><span class="font-semibold">Real Example:</span> Visit etherscan.io and look at the current gas fees for Ethereum transactions. Watch how they change throughout the day - just like how concert ticket prices fluctuate based on demand!</p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700"><span class="font-semibold">Quick Exercise:</span> Compare the energy impact: Calculate that one Bitcoin PoW transaction uses about 2,264.93 kWh (enough to power your home theater for 2.5 months!), while Ethereum's new PoS system uses 99.9% less energy (like switching from a stadium concert to an unplugged session). This shows why many networks are moving to PoS! 🌱</p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700"><span class="font-semibold">Understanding Why:</span> Just like how the music industry needs both record labels (centralized) and independent artists (decentralized), crypto needs robust systems to maintain security and trust. Mining and consensus mechanisms are like the music industry's quality control - they ensure every "release" (transaction) is authentic and valuable! 🎸</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- Crypto 102 Section -->
                <div id="crypto102" class="tab-content" style="display: none;">
                    <div class="mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-200 to-purple-200 p-6 rounded-lg border border-pink-300 flex items-center shadow-md">
                        <div class="mr-4">
                            <i data-lucide="rocket" class="text-pink-500" style="width: 50px; height: 50px;"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-pink-700">Crypto 102: Level Up Your Knowledge</h3>
                            <p>Ready to dive deeper? Like Beyoncé evolving from Destiny's Child to Renaissance, let's explore more advanced crypto concepts! 💫</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-50 to-pink-100 p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                        <h3 class="font-bold flex items-center text-pink-700">
                            <i data-lucide="code" class="mr-2" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"></i>
                            Smart Contracts & dApps: The New Hit Makers
                        </h3>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-white p-3 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Technical Definitions:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Smart Contracts:</span> Self-executing contracts with terms directly written into code.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">dApps:</span> Decentralized applications that run on blockchain networks.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Tokens:</span> Digital assets created and managed by smart contracts.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-pink-50 p-3 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Smart Contracts:</span> Like Ariana Grande's recording contract, but automated and transparent - when certain conditions are met (like hitting streaming milestones), payments happen automatically! 📝</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">dApps:</span> Like decentralized Spotify, where artists can release music directly to fans without a middleman! 🎧</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Tokens:</span> Like digital fan club memberships that give you special access and perks to your favorite artist's content! 🎟️</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-white p-3 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Try it yourself:</p>
                            <div class="space-y-2">
                                <p class="text-gray-700"><span class="font-semibold">Real Example:</span> Visit Uniswap (a popular dApp) and explore how it automatically swaps tokens using smart contracts - it's like a digital DJ automatically mixing tracks based on the crowd's energy! No human intermediary needed.</p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700"><span class="font-semibold">Quick Exercise:</span> Create a simple smart contract on Remix IDE (remix.ethereum.org) that automatically sends a token when someone pays 0.1 ETH - like creating an automated ticket booth that instantly delivers digital concert passes! 🎫</p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700"><span class="font-semibold">Bonus Challenge:</span> Find a popular NFT project on OpenSea and look at its smart contract on Etherscan. See how it manages token distribution - just like how streaming platforms distribute royalties to artists! 🎨</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-50 to-pink-100 p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                        <h3 class="font-bold flex items-center text-pink-700">
                            <i data-lucide="trending-up" class="mr-2" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"></i>
                            Market Dynamics: The Charts & Stats
                        </h3>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-white p-3 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Technical Definitions:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Market Capitalization:</span> Total value of a cryptocurrency, calculated by price × circulating supply.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Volatility:</span> The tendency for prices to fluctuate significantly.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Trading Pairs:</span> Two assets that can be traded for each other (e.g., BTC/USD).</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Liquidity:</span> How easily an asset can be bought or sold without affecting its price.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-pink-50 p-3 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Market Cap:</span> Like an artist's total streaming numbers across all platforms - it shows their overall impact and reach in the industry! 📊</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Volatility:</span> Like Taylor's chart positions going up and down with each new release - sometimes you're #1, sometimes you're cooling off! 📈</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Trading Pairs:</span> Like remix collaborations - you're trading one artist's style for another to create something new! 🎵</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Liquidity:</span> Like having enough fans ready to buy concert tickets at any price - the more fans, the easier it is to sell tickets without crashing the price! 🎟️</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-50 to-pink-100 p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                        <h3 class="font-bold flex items-center text-pink-700">
                            <i data-lucide="git-fork" class="mr-2" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"></i>
                            Exchanges & Forks: The Venues & Remixes
                        </h3>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-white p-3 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Technical Definitions:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Centralized Exchanges (CEX):</span> Traditional platforms operated by a central authority.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Decentralized Exchanges (DEX):</span> Platforms that operate without intermediaries.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Hard Fork:</span> A major protocol change creating a new blockchain.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Soft Fork:</span> A backward-compatible protocol update.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-pink-50 p-3 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">CEX:</span> Like major record labels with strict rules and security - everything goes through their approval process! 🏢</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">DEX:</span> Like underground music venues where artists and fans trade directly - no middleman needed! 🎸</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Hard Fork:</span> Like when Miley Cyrus completely changed from Hannah Montana to Bangerz - a totally new direction that creates two different paths! 🎭</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Soft Fork:</span> Like when Ariana Grande added R&B influences to her pop sound - an upgrade that still works with her original style! 🎤</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- Uniswap Section -->
                <div id="uniswap" class="tab-content" style="display: none;">
                    <div class="mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-200 to-purple-200 p-6 rounded-lg border border-pink-300 flex items-center shadow-md">
                        <div class="mr-4">
                            <i data-lucide="coins" class="text-pink-500" style="width: 50px; height: 50px;"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-pink-700">The Uniswap Phenomenon</h3>
                            <p>Just as pop stars like Megan Thee Stallion and Billie Eilish revolutionized the music industry, Uniswap changed how we trade crypto forever!</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-50 to-pink-100 p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                        <h3 class="font-bold flex items-center text-pink-700">
                            <i data-lucide="sparkles" class="mr-2" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"></i>
                            The Uniswap Origin Story
                        </h3>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-white p-3 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Technical Definition:</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">Uniswap is a decentralized exchange (DEX) protocol built on the Ethereum blockchain. It uses an automated market maker (AMM) system instead of traditional order books, allowing users to trade cryptocurrencies directly from their wallets without intermediaries. The protocol is governed by UNI token holders and has become one of the most widely used DEXs in the DeFi ecosystem.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="mt-3 pop-explanation p-3 rounded-lg">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-white">Now explain it in pop terms:</p>
                            <p class="text-white">Uniswap's journey is like Ariana Grande's rise from a Nickelodeon star to global pop icon. Created by Hayden Adams in 2018, Uniswap started as a simple experiment based on an idea proposed by Ethereum founder Vitalik Buterin.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-white p-3 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Uniswap Timeline:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">November 2018:</span> Uniswap V1 launches with a $100k grant from the Ethereum Foundation</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">May 2020:</span> Uniswap V2 introduces direct ERC-20 to ERC-20 pairs</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">September 2020:</span> UNI token launch with a retroactive airdrop to all past users</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">May 2021:</span> Uniswap V3 debuts with concentrated liquidity</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-50 to-pink-100 p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                        <h3 class="font-bold flex items-center text-pink-700">
                            <i data-lucide="coins" class="mr-2" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"></i>
                            Automated Market Maker: The Taylor Swift Revolution
                        </h3>
                        <div class="mt-3 technical-definition p-3 rounded-lg">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Technical Definition:</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">An Automated Market Maker (AMM) is a type of decentralized exchange protocol that relies on mathematical formulas to price assets. Instead of using order books, AMMs use liquidity pools where users can deposit pairs of tokens. The price of assets is determined by a constant product formula (x * y = k), where x and y represent the quantities of two tokens in a pool, and k is a constant. This system allows for continuous trading without the need for matching buyers and sellers.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="mt-3 pop-explanation p-3 rounded-lg">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-white">Now explain it in pop terms:</p>
                            <p class="text-white">Uniswap's AMM model is like how Charli XCX revolutionized the music industry by taking control of her career and embracing hyperpop. Traditional exchanges use order books where buyers and sellers match up directly, but Uniswap uses liquidity pools and a mathematical formula to set prices automatically.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Trading Terms Section -->
                <div id="trading" class="tab-content" style="display: none;">
                    <div class="mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-200 to-purple-200 p-6 rounded-lg border border-pink-300 flex items-center shadow-md">
                        <div class="mr-4">
                            <i data-lucide="trending-up" class="text-pink-500" style="width: 50px; height: 50px;"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-pink-700">Crypto Trading: The Pop Charts of Finance</h3>
                            <p>Just like how pop songs from artists like Chappell Roan and Gracie Abrams climb and fall on the charts, crypto prices move up and down. Let's learn the language of trading!</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-50 to-pink-100 p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                        <h3 class="font-bold flex items-center text-pink-700">
                            <i data-lucide="chart-line" class="mr-2" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"></i>
                            Market Terms: The Billboard Hot 100 of Crypto
                        </h3>
                        <div class="mt-3 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-pink-700">Bull Market</h4>
                                <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                                    <span class="font-semibold">Technical Definition:</span> A market condition where prices are rising or expected to rise, typically characterized by increased buying activity and positive investor sentiment.
                                </div>
                                <div class="mt-2 bg-pink-50 p-2 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                    <span class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</span>
                                    <p class="text-sm">Like when Sabrina Carpenter's album drops and all her songs shoot to the top of the charts. A period when prices are rising and optimism is high.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-pink-700">Bear Market</h4>
                                <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                                    <span class="font-semibold">Technical Definition:</span> A market condition where prices are falling or expected to fall, typically characterized by increased selling activity and negative investor sentiment.
                                </div>
                                <div class="mt-2 bg-pink-50 p-2 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                    <span class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</span>
                                    <p class="text-sm">Like when a pop star's album underperforms. A period when prices are falling and pessimism prevails.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-pink-700">Market Cap</h4>
                                <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                                    <span class="font-semibold">Technical Definition:</span> The total market value of a cryptocurrency, calculated by multiplying the current price by the total number of coins in circulation.
                                </div>
                                <div class="mt-2 bg-pink-50 p-2 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                    <span class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</span>
                                    <p class="text-sm">Like Doechii's total streams across all platforms. The total value of all coins in circulation (price × circulating supply).</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-pink-700">Volume</h4>
                                <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                                    <span class="font-semibold">Technical Definition:</span> The total amount of cryptocurrency traded within a specific time period, indicating the level of market activity and liquidity.
                                </div>
                                <div class="mt-2 bg-pink-50 p-2 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                    <span class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</span>
                                    <p class="text-sm">Like the number of streams Megan Thee Stallion's songs get. The total amount of trading activity in a given period.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-50 to-pink-100 p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                        <h3 class="font-bold flex items-center text-pink-700">
                            <i data-lucide="activity" class="mr-2" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"></i>
                            Trading Strategies: The Producer's Playbook
                        </h3>
                        <div class="mt-3 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-pink-700">HODL</h4>
                                <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                                    <span class="font-semibold">Technical Definition:</span> A long-term investment strategy where investors hold onto their cryptocurrency regardless of market volatility, based on the belief in the long-term value of the asset.
                                </div>
                                <div class="mt-2 bg-pink-50 p-2 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                    <span class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</span>
                                    <p class="text-sm">Like when Billie Eilish holds onto her masters. Holding onto your crypto despite market fluctuations.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-pink-700">DCA (Dollar-Cost Averaging)</h4>
                                <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                                    <span class="font-semibold">Technical Definition:</span> An investment strategy where an investor divides the total amount to be invested across periodic purchases of a target asset to reduce the impact of volatility on the overall purchase.
                                </div>
                                <div class="mt-2 bg-pink-50 p-2 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                    <span class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</span>
                                    <p class="text-sm">Like releasing singles gradually instead of dropping a whole album at once. Investing fixed amounts at regular intervals regardless of price.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-pink-700">FOMO (Fear of Missing Out)</h4>
                                <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                                    <span class="font-semibold">Technical Definition:</span> A psychological phenomenon where investors make impulsive decisions to buy assets due to the fear of missing out on potential gains, often leading to buying at peak prices.
                                </div>
                                <div class="mt-2 bg-pink-50 p-2 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                    <span class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</span>
                                    <p class="text-sm">Like rushing to buy concert tickets when Ariana Grande announces a tour. Making impulsive investment decisions based on market hype.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-pink-700">DYOR (Do Your Own Research)</h4>
                                <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                                    <span class="font-semibold">Technical Definition:</span> A principle emphasizing the importance of conducting thorough research and analysis before making investment decisions, rather than relying solely on others' advice or market hype.
                                </div>
                                <div class="mt-2 bg-pink-50 p-2 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                    <span class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</span>
                                    <p class="text-sm">Like reading reviews before buying concert tickets. Making informed decisions based on thorough research.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-50 to-pink-100 p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                        <h3 class="font-bold flex items-center text-pink-700">
                            <i data-lucide="shield" class="mr-2" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"></i>
                            Risk Management: The Tour Manager's Guide
                        </h3>
                        <div class="mt-3 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-pink-700">Stop-Loss</h4>
                                <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                                    <span class="font-semibold">Technical Definition:</span> A risk management tool that automatically sells an asset when it reaches a predetermined price level to limit potential losses.
                                </div>
                                <div class="mt-2 bg-pink-50 p-2 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                    <span class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</span>
                                    <p class="text-sm">Like having a backup plan for a Charli XCX concert. An order to sell if the price drops to a certain level to limit losses.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-pink-700">Take-Profit</h4>
                                <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                                    <span class="font-semibold">Technical Definition:</span> A risk management tool that automatically sells an asset when it reaches a predetermined price level to secure profits.
                                </div>
                                <div class="mt-2 bg-pink-50 p-2 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                    <span class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</span>
                                    <p class="text-sm">Like knowing when to end a Chappell Roan concert. An order to sell when the price reaches a certain profit target.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-pink-700">Position Sizing</h4>
                                <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                                    <span class="font-semibold">Technical Definition:</span> The process of determining the appropriate amount of capital to allocate to a particular investment based on risk tolerance and portfolio size.
                                </div>
                                <div class="mt-2 bg-pink-50 p-2 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                    <span class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</span>
                                    <p class="text-sm">Like planning a Gracie Abrams tour budget. Determining how much to invest in a particular asset based on your total portfolio.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-pink-700">Diversification</h4>
                                <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                                    <span class="font-semibold">Technical Definition:</span> An investment strategy that involves spreading investments across different assets, sectors, or strategies to reduce overall portfolio risk.
                                </div>
                                <div class="mt-2 bg-pink-50 p-2 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                    <span class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</span>
                                    <p class="text-sm">Like having multiple hit songs from different genres. Spreading investments across different assets to reduce risk.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-50 to-pink-100 p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                        <h3 class="font-bold flex items-center text-pink-700">
                            <i data-lucide="zap" class="mr-2" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"></i>
                            DeFi Trading Terms: The Remix Edition
                        </h3>
                        <div class="mt-3 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-pink-700">Liquidity Pool</h4>
                                <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                                    <span class="font-semibold">Technical Definition:</span> A collection of funds locked in a smart contract that provides liquidity for trading on decentralized exchanges, enabling users to swap between different tokens.
                                </div>
                                <div class="mt-2 bg-pink-50 p-2 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                    <span class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</span>
                                    <p class="text-sm">Like a concert venue's capacity for a Doechii show. A pool of tokens locked in a smart contract that enables trading on DEXs.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-pink-700">Impermanent Loss</h4>
                                <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                                    <span class="font-semibold">Technical Definition:</span> A temporary loss of funds experienced by liquidity providers in automated market maker (AMM) pools when the price of deposited tokens changes compared to when they were deposited.
                                </div>
                                <div class="mt-2 bg-pink-50 p-2 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                    <span class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</span>
                                    <p class="text-sm">Like when a Megan Thee Stallion concert gets rescheduled. Temporary loss experienced by liquidity providers due to price changes.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-pink-700">APY (Annual Percentage Yield)</h4>
                                <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                                    <span class="font-semibold">Technical Definition:</span> The real rate of return earned on an investment, taking into account the effect of compounding interest. In DeFi, it represents the annualized return on investment from providing liquidity or staking tokens.
                                </div>
                                <div class="mt-2 bg-pink-50 p-2 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                    <span class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</span>
                                    <p class="text-sm">Like an artist's yearly earnings from streams and tours. The real rate of return earned on an investment, including compound interest.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-pink-700">Gas Fees</h4>
                                <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                                    <span class="font-semibold">Technical Definition:</span> The fee required to successfully conduct a transaction or execute a contract on the Ethereum blockchain, paid in ETH to compensate miners for the computational resources used.
                                </div>
                                <div class="mt-2 bg-pink-50 p-2 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
                                    <span class="font-semibold text-pink-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</span>
                                    <p class="text-sm">Like ticket processing fees for a Billie Eilish concert. The cost required to perform a transaction on the Ethereum network.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
