                            NFTs & Digital Ownership: The VIP Experience
                        </h3>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-white p-3 rounded-lg border border-purple-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Technical Definitions:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">NFT Standards:</span> Technical specifications like ERC-721 and ERC-1155 that define how NFTs work.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Metadata:</span> Additional information stored with NFTs describing their properties.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Minting:</span> The process of creating new NFTs on the blockchain.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold">Royalties:</span> Automatic payments to creators when their NFTs are resold.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="mt-3 bg-purple-50 p-3 rounded-lg border border-purple-200">
                            <p class="font-semibold text-purple-700">Now explain it in pop terms:</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">NFTs are like VIP backstage passes that can't be copied! Just like how each Taylor Swift Eras Tour ticket is unique, each NFT has special properties. Minting NFTs is like pressing limited edition vinyl records, and royalties are like artists getting paid every time their song gets played!</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-50 to-purple-100 p-4 rounded-lg border border-purple-200">
